    • Method Detail

      • compose

        public static <A,B,C> Function<A,C> compose(Function<A,B> f1,
                                            Function<B,C> f2)
        Returns a Function that composes the specified Functions with chained Function.andThen(Function). It is useful when you need to compose method handles, which is impossible with Function.andThen(Function): 
        
 Function<A, B> f = Functions.compose(TypeA::new, TypeB::new);
